<p>boy's waiting for us to land  we had no sooner set our foot on shore than we were rushed by these imps each clamouring for us to take their particular donk as he was the best there after a lot of arguing &amp; shouting each rider was satisfied,  &amp; armed with a big stick &amp; a donkey boy to keep him going off we went, we had not gone far before the quiet ride developed into a mad race nurses &amp; all joining in talk about croppers every few yards some one would be down either the donkey would fall &amp; bring half a dozen with him or the saddle would slip &amp; off you would go, just imagine this crowd racing along</p>
